  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      402.54,
      506.04,
      429.62
    ],
    "text": "Traffic Advisory for the Annual Theru Festival of Arulmigu Sri Muttumari Amman Temple \u2013 Matale Police Division",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      444.06,
      519.19,
      484.94
    ],
    "text": "The annual Theru festival of the Arulmigu Sri Muttumari Amman Temple in Matale city is scheduled to commence on 02.03.2026 at 6:00 a.m., with five Theru chariots planned to tour the streets of Matale until 6:00 p.m. on 03.03.2026.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      499.5,
      523.14,
      554.18
    ],
    "text": "Devotees and foreign tourists from across the island are expected to attend the festival to witness the celebrations and seek blessings. Additionally, several amusement parks in Matale city will be operating simultaneously, which may result in heavy traffic congestion during this period.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      568.77,
      498.87,
      595.85
    ],
    "text": "To facilitate smooth traffic flow, the Matale Police Division requests motorists traveling between Dambulla and Kandy via Matale town to use the following alternative routes:",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      610.29,
      514.78,
      623.57
    ],
    "text": "Alternative Routes for Vehicles Traveling from Kandy to Dambulla via Matale Town:",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      638.13,
      513.75,
      679.01
    ],
    "text": "\u2022 From Kumbiyangoda Road, turn left near the Kumbiyangoda Bridge onto Hulangamuwa Road, then continue along King\u2019s Street in Matale town and turn left toward Dambulla.",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "SymbolMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.960000038146973,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      693.45,
      514.78,
      706.73
    ],
    "text": "Alternative Routes for Vehicles Traveling from Dambulla to Kandy via Matale Town:",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      721.29,
      506.43,
      762.19
    ],
    "text": "\u2022 From Thotagamuwa Junction, turn left onto Imbulandanda Road, then from Kanangamuwa Junction, travel along Parawaththa Road south to Kaludewala. Continue on Ratthota Road to the left to Weragama, turn right, proceed via Kivula",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "SymbolMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.960000038146973,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      45.47,
      493.23,
      72.55
    ],
    "text": "onto Matale Gongawela Road, turn left, then enter the Matale\u2013Kandy Road and continue toward Kandy.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      87.13,
      333.31,
      100.41
    ],
    "text": "Special Traffic Arrangements During the Festival:",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      114.85,
      524.85,
      183.33
    ],
    "text": "\u2022 On 02.03.2026, when the chariots are traveling along the main street in central Matale, traffic will be diverted along King\u2019s Street in both directions toward Dambulla and Kandy. \u2022 On 03.03.2026, when the chariots are on King\u2019s Street, traffic will be routed along the main street in both directions toward Dambulla and Kandy.",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "SymbolMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.960000038146973,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      197.89,
      523.33,
      224.97
    ],
    "text": "The Matale Police request media institutions to disseminate this information widely to ensure motorists and the public are informed and can plan their travel accordingly.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
